Install the XpIde
=================

Step by step:
 - Copy or link all files from <xp.ide dir>/bin to
   your ${HOME}/bin directory.

     cp <xp.ide dir>/bin/* ~/bin/
   
   Contents:
     * gx: gedit starter which takes fully qualified
           classnames as arguments.
	   Offers an autocompletion.
     * nx: like gx, but for nedit
     * xpide: XpIde shell runner (mandatory)
     * xp.ide.bashrc: bashrc extension file which
           provides the bash autocompletion for gx an nx,
	   an alias for nedit to load all nedit extensions
	   and sets the environment variable for the
	   XpIde class path (XP_IDE_CP)


 - Copy or link all files and directories from <xp.ide dir>/gedit
   to your gedit plugin directory (${HOME}/.gnome2/gedit/plugins).
   
     cp -r <xp.ide dir>/gedit/* ~/.gnome2/gedit/plugins/
   
   Contents:
     * xpide.gedit-plugin: gedit plugin definition
     * xpide: python source package


 - Copy or link all files from <xp.ide dir>/nedit
   to your nedit settings directory (${HOME}/.nedit/).
   
     cp -r <xp.ide dir>/nedit/* ~/.nedit/
   
   Contents:
     * xp.ide.menu:   menu and shortcut definitions
     * xp.ide.nm:     macro definitions
     * xp.ide.theme:  color theme
     * xp.php.syntax: syntax highlighting for PHP and XP


 - Copy or link the <xp.ide dir>/lib directory to your ${HOME}/xp
   directory. If you want to set it elsewhere, you have to provide
   the path in the "XP_IDE_CP" environment variable.
   
     cp -r <xp.ide dir>/lib ~/xp/
   
   Contents:
     * xp-ide-<version>.xar: XpIde classes


 - Add the following lines to you ${HOME}/.bashrc file to load it
   when bash starts up:
   <code>
     if [ -f $HOME/bin/xp.ide.bashrc ]; then
	 . $HOME/bin/xp.ide.bashrc
     fi
   </code>
   
     echo "" >> ~/.bashrc
     echo "# Load XpIde bash extension and set environment" >> ~/.bashrc
     echo "if [ -f \$HOME/bin/xp.ide.bashrc ]; then . \$HOME/bin/xp.ide.bashrc; fi" >> ~/.bashrc


- Add the following line to your ${HOME}/.nedit/autoload.nm file
  to load the needed nedit macros when nedit starts up:
  <code>
    load_macro_file(getenv("HOME") "/.nedit/xp.ide.nm")
  </code>
  
    echo "load_macro_file(getenv(\"HOME\") \"/.nedit/xp.ide.nm\")" >> ~/.nedit/autoload.nm

